{
    "title": "Gorgonzola Popovers",
    "categories": ["Appetizers"],
    "servings": {
        "count": 24,
        "size": {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "mini popover"}
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "markdown": [
                "## Ingredients"
            ]
        },
        {
            "ingredients": [
                {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "large eggs"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "room temperature milk"},
                {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "melted butter"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                {"amount": 0.125, "unit": "tsp", "name": "ground black pepper"},
                {"amount": 1.25, "unit": "oz", "name": "Gorgonzola cheese"},
                {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "chopped fresh thyme"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "markdown": [
                "## Instructions",
                "",
                "1. Whisk together eggs, milk, melted butter, flour, salt, pepper, and thyme and refrigerate for 2 hours.",
                "",
                "2. Stir-in Gorgonzola cheese and thyme",
                "",
                "3. Butter 2 mini muffin pans. Fill each cup to the top with batter.",
                "",
                "Adjust the oven rack to the highest position in oven and bake at 425 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes",
                "until puffed and golden.",
                "",
                "Great served as an appetizer with red wine."
            ]
        }
    ]
}
